<subSubSection id="D6B9258EC66AFF9B2A9C9A2D37C17F49" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C66AFF9B2A9C9A2D37C17F49" blockId="30.[151,1437,1407,2009]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C66AFF9B2A9C9A2D32037CF9" bold="true" box="[151,273,1407,1432]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from most similar known relative (
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C66AFF9B294A9AD330D27CF9" authorityName=": Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[833,960,1409,1432]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C66AFF9B294A9AD330D27CF9" box="[833,960,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">M. cyaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by wider and shorter procursus (compare 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C66AFF9B2A9C9AF632737CDD" box="[151,353,1444,1469]" captionStart="FIGURES96–103" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1872,1894]" captionTargetBox="[157,1417,377,1849]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,373,1850]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES96–103.Left procursi, prolateraland retrolateral views.96–97.Mesabolivar macushi sp.n.(ZFMK Ar 18962).98– 99. M. aurantiacus (Mello-Leitão, 1930) (ZFMK Ar 18963). 100–101. M. cyaneus (Taczanowski, 1874) (ZFMK Ar 18989). 102–103.M.spinosus (González-Sponga, 2005) (MIZA MAGS 1176). Scale line:0.5 (all at same scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202543/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 101 and 103</figureCitation>
), by bulbal process with complex distal structures (compare 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C66AFF9B2E109AF637F17CDD" box="[1051,1251,1444,1469]" captionStart="FIGURES 104–114" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1784]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 104–114. Left bulbal processes, dorsal and prolatero-ventral views (104–111), epigynum, ventral and lateral views (112–113), andcleared female genitalia,dorsal view (114). 104–105.Mesabolivar macushi sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18962).106–107. M. aurantiacus (Mello-Leitão, 1930) (ZFMK Ar 18963). 108–109. M.cyaneus (Taczanowski, 1874) (ZFMK Ar 18989). 110– 114.M.spinosus (González-Sponga, 2005) (MIZA MAGS 1176). Scale lines: 0.5 (all bubal processes at same scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202545/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 109 and 111</figureCitation>
), and by female external and internal genitalia (epigynum wider; relatively larger internal sclerotized structure, compare 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C66AFF9B2F3F9A9533D27F65" captionStart="FIGURES 104–114" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1784]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 104–114. Left bulbal processes, dorsal and prolatero-ventral views (104–111), epigynum, ventral and lateral views (112–113), andcleared female genitalia,dorsal view (114). 104–105.Mesabolivar macushi sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18962).106–107. M. aurantiacus (Mello-Leitão, 1930) (ZFMK Ar 18963). 108–109. M.cyaneus (Taczanowski, 1874) (ZFMK Ar 18989). 110– 114.M.spinosus (González-Sponga, 2005) (MIZA MAGS 1176). Scale lines: 0.5 (all bubal processes at same scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202545/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 112, 114</figureCitation>
and Huber 2000: figs 799–800); from 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C66AFF9B287D9ABF30307F65" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1930" box="[630,802,1517,1540]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Blechroscelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantiacus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C66AFF9B287D9ABF30307F65" box="[630,802,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">M. aurantiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also by much wider palpal femur, by absence of ventral process on procursus, and by simple epigynal pocket (not extending anteriorly into long furrow).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
